About Me

I'm Sreehari, a 19-year-old BTEC Mechanical Engineering student in my third semester at College of Engineering Pathanapuram, Kerala, India. My world sits at the intersection of engineering logic and creative instinct — I spend as much time designing visuals and editing photos as I do studying CAD and thermodynamics. Industry 4.0 is pulling mechanical engineering into the digital age, and I'm pulling with it — exploring how IoT, AI, and smart manufacturing connect to the physical systems I study. I'm here at μFIFA to build a real public portfolio, find my squad, and prove that a mechanical engineer can also be a damn good designer. The pitch is where ideas get tested. Let's go.


